article.headline: VA Commonwealth 70, Drexel 69
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jesse Pellot-Rosa's layup with 6 seconds remaining gave Virginia Commonwealth a 70-69 victory over Drexel on Saturday. Dominic Jones had 21 points to lead the Rams (12-5, 6-2 Colonial Athletic Association), who have won five of their last six games. Troy Goodwin had 15 points and Michael Doles added 12. Tim Whitworth scored 17 points and Phil Goss had 15 for the Dragons (9-7, 4-2), who had all five starters score in double figures. Drexel went scoreless for 6:26 down the stretch but was still within two points after Whitworth hit a 3-pointer with 26 seconds left. After Doles missed the front end of a 1-and-1, Goss came free off a screen and hit a 3 from the corner to give the Dragons a one-point lead. But Pellot-Rosa streaked past Whitworth on the inbounds pass and finished the play with a layup. Bashir Mason of Drexel could not get a shot off before time expired. Drexel guard Jeremiah King missed the game after dislocating his shoulder Wednesday. He'll be out indefinitely.
